<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12005d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12005d">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12005d"> 5(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> ~ marks of his claws</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Une quantit&eacute; de pierres, emport&eacute;es par Lucifer pour b&acirc;tir le Mont, ont &eacute;t&eacute; abandonn&eacute;es par lui o&ugrave; on les voit aujourd&apos;hui, parce que, ayant mal fait ses calculs, il y en avait assez; et les rainures, les cavit&eacute;s que pr&eacute;sentent certains de ces menhirs sont les empreintes de sa queue, de ses griffes, ou de ses cornes. <br><font color="green">[A quantity of rocks, brought by Lucifer to build the Mount, were abandoned by him where we see them today because, having miscalculated, he already had enough of them. The grooves, the cavities on some of these menhirs, are the marks of his tail, his claws, or his horns.]</font> <small> l'Abb&eacute; A. Millon, <a name="AMPB" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#AMPB"><cite title="source">Pauvres Pierres! Les Megalithes Bretons devant la science</cite></a> (n.d) 15</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
